{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e608a19a-e9a5-41cb-93e6-9f7e66da3d1d","content":"No files exist in the workspace, so I'll walk you through the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\n**1. Add `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage`:**\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Picker Title=\"Theme\"\n                SelectedItem=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Notifications\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n        <HorizontalStackLayout Spacing=\"10\">\n            <Label Text=\"Font Size\" VerticalOptions=\"Center\" />\n            <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\"\n                     Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"36\" Increment=\"1\" />\n            <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='{0}pt'}\" />\n        </HorizontalStackLayout>\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only XAML change** is adding the `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` attribute. This tells the compiler the type of `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding …}` is resolved at compile time instead of at runtime via reflection.\n\n**2. Catch binding errors at build time — add this to your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat broken bindings as compiler errors -->\n  <MauiStrictXamlCompilation>true</MauiStrictXamlCompilation>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nWith `x:DataType` set, the XAML compiler will now **emit a build error** if you reference a property that doesn't exist on `SettingsViewModel` (e.g., a typo like `{Binding Thme}`).\n\n## Key points\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **What triggers compilation** | `x:DataType` on any element; all child bindings inherit it |\n| **Opt out locally** | `x:DataType=\"\"` on a subtree to fall back to reflection |\n| **Performance** | Compiled bindings skip reflection — faster, less memory |\n| **Build errors** | Misspelled properties, wrong types, and missing paths are caught at `dotnet build` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f4900b4b-0379-4dda-9620-2c6261044b4b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking about a conceptual conversion of a .NET MAUI page. Since there are no files, I'll provide the answer directly with code examples showing how to convert to compiled bindings.","outputTokens":717,"requestId":"77CC:5FAF2:7DD6D59:8C01769:69EABD84"},"id":"58504af9-147b-4b34-b2fd-83890ee35981","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:47:14.657Z","parentId":"3508d40e-cb7f-460b-bb66-523a6501a6d5"}
